The tests failed because the doc is outdated, I'll push another commit soon.

I changed the config name and a class name(typo before), I think the changed config&class name have not been released ever, so it would not affect users. Please let me know if this behavior should be reverted.

This does seems to happen for `ContinuousProcessingTimeTrigger` too. Its clear method NPEs when clearing the window:

```java
	@Override
	public void clear(W window, TriggerContext ctx) throws Exception {
		ReducingState<Long> fireTimestamp = ctx.getPartitionedState(stateDesc);
		long timestamp = fireTimestamp.get();
		ctx.deleteProcessingTimeTimer(timestamp);
		fireTimestamp.clear();
	}
```
